The reaction products were analyzed with the
Q3D spectrograph and then detected in a 1m long
focal-plane detector with cathode strip readout, which
performed dE-Erest particle identification and position
determination.

For the energy calibration of spectra, wellknown
levels in 133Ba were used, as well as the 144Sm(d,p)
reaction, which was measured at 10.degr. with the same
magnetic settings as this spectrum, with a 49 mu-g/cm2
thick target on 16 mu-g/cm2 carbon backing.
This reaction provided very good calibration peaks
up to 2.3MeV excitation in our reaction.
The target consisted of 60 mu-g/cm2 of 132Ba
implanted in a 40 mu-g/cm2 carbon foil, and it was
produced at the SIDONIE isotope separator of
CSNSM-Orsay starting from BaCO3 material enriched
